verbose_text: High dose of chimeras (750 nmol/L), either naked or duplexed with the cationic liposome N-[1-(2,3-Dioleoyloxy) propyl]-N, N, N-trimethylammonium methyl-sulfate (DOTAP) targeting endosomal TLR7/8, failed to induce significant levels of IFN-alpha and TNF-alpha in PBMCs, unlike the known TLR7/8 ligand, a single stranded RNA XREF_BIBR.
